main event: Two objects were sighted in the sky at different times on June 15, 1966, in Clovis, New Mexico.
interesting points: The first object faded in the east while the second object appeared brighter than the first., The duration of observation for the first object was 5 minutes and for the second object was 10 minutes., The observer described the objects as resembling stars., The conclusion of the report categorized the objects as possibly being satellites., The weather conditions during the sightings were clear, contributing to visibility.
witness description: sales engineer, appeared reliable, not unduly concerned about the sighting
